cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE 

The paper introduces a parallel offline algorithm for computing hybrid conditional plans in a robotics application domain. The method relies on modeling actuation and sensing actions in an expressive nonmonotonic language of answer set programming (ASP) and utilizes nonmonotonic constructs and nondeterministic choices. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper introduces a new algorithm for planning in a robotics domain. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) as the paper focuses on a robotics application domain and proposes a method for planning in this domain. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as the paper utilizes answer set programming (ASP) for modeling actuation and sensing actions. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) as the paper introduces a new algorithm that relies on a specific programming language (ASP) for planning. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) as the paper presents a new method for planning that can be applied in software engineering for robotics applications.
